FT  11 NOV 93 / Radio group loses both Devon licences
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   A COMMERCIAL radio station owned by Capital Radio and GWR
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
two of the main companies in the industry - has lost both its broadcasting
licences.
The Radio Authority yesterday decided not to renew the licences of DevonAir
which broadcasts in the Exeter and Torbay area. It awarded both FM and AM
licences to Gemini Radio, a local consortium put together by Mr Ivor
Stolliday, a former secretary of the ITV Association and Television South
West; and Mr David Rogers, managing director of Orchard FM in Somerset.
