A COMMERCIAL radio station owned by Capital Radio and GWR two of the main
companies in the industry - has lost both its broadcasting licences.
The Radio Authority yesterday decided not to renew the licences of DevonAir
which broadcasts in the Exeter and Torbay area. It awarded both FM and AM
