proposals for two complementary AM and FM programme services'.
DevonAir appears to have lost because it broadcasts the same mainly
pop-orientated service on AM and FM. Gemini, which will take over in January
1995, plans to have at least 45 per cent speech on its AM service.
The authority will advertise the franchise for the mainly speech-based third
national commercial station on November 30.
</TEXT>
