<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 93 / Prosecutor acts on Polly Peck
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NICOSIA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
In a bizarre twist to the Polly Peck saga, a Turkish prosecutor has issued
an order for the arrest of administrators of the collapsed
fruit-to-electronics conglomerate on bribery charges, a lawyer for former
Polly Peck chairman Asil Nadir said yesterday, Reuter reports from Nicosia.
The lawyer, Ali Riza Gorgun, said he had received a copy of the arrest
warrant for the three main administrators - Richard Stone and Michael Jordan
of Coopers &amp; Lybrand and Christopher Morris of Touche Ross - and six of
their colleagues as well as their Turkish lawyer.
Mr Gorgun said the Istanbul prosecutor's office had acted on a complaint by
Mr Nadir about how the administrators had handled the affairs of Polly Peck.
A similar complaint had been lodged with the prosecutor's office in northern
Cyprus, he added.
Mr Nadir, who was charged with theft and false accounting following the
collapse of Polly Peck, jumped bail in Britain and fled to his native
northern Cyprus in May. He accuses the British authorities of mounting a
conspiracy to deny him a fair trial.
