<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 93 / World News in Brief: Seatbelt call after 10 die in coach
crash
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MPs, the RAC and the Consumers' Association last night demanded the
compulsory fitting of seatbelts in coaches. The call came after 10 people
died and many others were injured when a coach (above) carrying 44 US and
Canadian tourists from London to Canterbury skidded off the M2 motorway in
heavy rain near Faversham, Kent. In south-west France 13 motorists were
killed in a multiple crash after a tanker truck caught fire on the
Bordeaux-Paris motorway.
