<DATELINE>
   LOS ANGELES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A defendant in the Reginald Denny beating case agreed to plead guilty to two
misdemeanour charges and one felony count yesterday, in return for a
sentence of lengthy probation, Reuter reports from Los Angeles.
Mr Antoine Miller, 21, served 17 months in jail while awaiting trial
following the beating of Denny, a white truck driver, by a black mob at the
start of last year's riots.
