per cent, and that yesterday's results were 'a little duller than expected'.
They said next year's earnings would benefit from property developments in
the pipeline.
China Light said its sales of electricity to China have been affected by the
austerity measures introduced by the Chinese government to cool the
mainland's economy.
Total sales for the year amounted to 25,598m KW - up 10 per cent on last
year's - but the rate of increase in sales in the coming year was expected
to be lower.
