<HEADLINE>
FT  10 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Emerald Energy heads for USM
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT CORZINE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EMERALD Energy is to be introduced to the USM next week in a Pounds 1.7m
share placing which will follow a reverse takeover engineered by Mr Peter
Winton, the former exploration director of Tricent-rol.
Tricentrol made substantial discoveries in the North Sea in the 1980s before
being bought by Arco, the US oil company.
Emerald Energy is based on the Isle of Man. It will place 170m new shares at
1p each through brokers John Siddall and Son, and Walker, Crips, Weddle,
Beck. Trading will begin next Tuesday. Its shares have traded under Rule
535(2).
Mr Iain Alexander, who will take over as chairman, says the bulk of the
Pounds 1.51m Emerald intends to raise will be used to develop US oil and gas
assets acquired from Mr Winton's Cobham Oil and Gas for Pounds 500,000 in
shares and options.
The 46 wells on 4,200 acres of land in west Virginia are located in the
Appalachian Basin, where oil and gas have been produced since the late
1800s.
Many of the wells are not in production, but Mr Winton, who takes over as
managing director of Emerald, says a combination of deepening existing wells
and drilling 120 new ones nearby 'will open up significant reserves'.
Emerald's strategy is to take advantage of the recent deregulation of the US
natural gas industry and the higher prices which have ensued by seeking
additional acquisitions of existing fields whose output can be increased
without big capital investment.
</TEXT>
