<HEADLINE>
FT  10 NOV 93 / Mercury launches charge cards
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COMPETITION in the fast-growing market for telephone charge cards was given
a boost yesterday with the launch of a range of cards by Mercury
Communications, the main competitor to British Telecommunications.
Mercury said its cards offered 'substantial savings' on long-distance
tariffs compared with BT's Chargecard. It also offered new features such as
the capacity to call from abroad without using an operator.
Charge cards allow customers to use pay phones and private handsets other
than their own and charge the cost to their home account, or that of their
company.
Mercury's long-distance charge card tariffs are generally lower than BT's
standard tariffs, but BT last week made sharp cuts in its weekend tariffs
for long-distance charge card users. BT also claims to have charge card
agreements with more international operators than Mercury.
