<HEADLINE>
FT  09 NOV 93 / Women boost student numbers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE EXPANSION in university student numbers has been fuelled by extra women
taking places to read arts courses, statistics published yesterday show.
'Old' universities - which excludes those that have gained university status
in the past two years - expanded by 33 per cent in the four years to
1992-93.
Women made up 47 per cent of full-time undergraduates compared with 41 per
cent 10 years earlier. But only 22 per cent of academic staff were women (14
per cent a decade earlier).
Students and Staff. Universities' Statistical Record, PO Box 130,
Cheltenham, Glos GL50 3SE. Pounds 16.50.
